## Biological Interpretation

### PfAlba1 — Core RBP, constitutively expressed
High detection (26.6% cells, 15,055 total UMIs) across all stages with trophozoite peak. Consistent with known role as translational regulator throughout the intraerythrocytic cycle. Confirmed by both scRNA-seq and bulk TPM data.

### PfAlba2 — Dominant RBP, highest expression of all four
Highest detection of the family (42.9% cells, 28,279 UMIs). Peaks in ring and trophozoite stages. Known to interact with RUF6 ncRNA (an activator of var expression). Overexpression represses var genes (Acharya et al. 2025). Confirmed by both scRNA-seq and bulk TPM.

### PfAlba3 — Near-absent in scRNA-seq; dropout confirmed
Only 484 cells (1.4%) detect Alba3, with a maximum of 3 UMIs per cell. However, **bulk RNA-seq (TPM analysis) shows Alba3 peaks at 40–44 hpi (late trophozoite/early schizont)**. The discrepancy is explained by **scRNA-seq dropout**: each droplet captures only 5–15% of a cell's mRNA, so lowly-expressed transcripts get zero counts by chance. This is a known limitation of scRNA-seq technology.

### PfAlba4 — Near-absent across all stages
Only 52 cells (0.15%) express Alba4, randomly distributed across stages with no enrichment. Bulk TPM shows Alba4 is expressed at 40–48 hpi and in merozoites. Same dropout explanation applies. Overexpression is well-tolerated by the parasite and does not significantly perturb the transcriptome (Acharya et al. 2025), consistent with its role in the non-essential NMD pathway.

