## Technical Notes

### Why scRNA-seq and bulk RNA-seq disagree for Alba3/4
scRNA-seq dropout is the primary explanation. For a gene with very few transcripts per cell, the probability that any given droplet captures at least one molecule of that mRNA is low. Bulk RNA-seq averages signal across millions of cells, accumulating enough signal even from rare transcripts to yield a reliable measurement. This is not a pipeline error — it is an inherent property of the technology.

### Gene name format in this dataset
This dataset uses **hyphens** in PlasmoDB IDs: `PF3D7-0813600`  
Standard PlasmoDB format uses **underscores**: `PF3D7_0813600`  
Using underscores will return "gene not found" in this dataset.

### Why DotPlot uses scale = FALSE
With only 4 stage groups, z-score scaling (the default in Seurat's DotPlot) compresses relative differences and generates a misleading color scale ranging from -1 to +1. Using `scale = FALSE` displays actual log-normalized expression values.

